---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Privacy Policy"
	description="Privacy Policy for alienzj's personal tools and vdirsyncer integration."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-04-22')}
    category="Legal"
>
	<div class="legal-container">
		<p>
            This Privacy Policy describes how your personal information is handled when you use 
            <strong>vdirsyncer</strong> (a third-party CLI tool) in conjunction with 
            Google Cloud APIs configured by <strong>alienzj</strong> for personal use.
		</p>

		<section>
			<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
			<p>
				Our integration with Google Cloud APIs (specifically the Google Calendar API) is designed 
                to facilitate the synchronization of calendar data using <code>vdirsyncer</code>. 
                When you authorize this application, it may access your Google Calendar data.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
			<p>
				The access granted to Google Calendar is used solely for the purpose of 
                synchronizing your calendar events with your local machine or other personal 
                servers as configured in your <code>vdirsyncer</code> setup.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>3. Data Storage and Security</h2>
			<p>
				<strong>We do not store your data on any external servers.</strong> 
                All calendar data retrieved via the API is processed locally on your machine. 
                The OAuth tokens used to access the API are stored locally on your device 
                and are never transmitted to us or any third party.
			</p>
		</section>

        <section>
			<h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
			<p>
				We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information 
                to outside parties. Your data remains entirely under your control.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>5. Revoking Access</h2>
			<p>
				You can revoke the application's access to your Google account at any time 
                through your <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Account Security settings</a>.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>6. Contact</h2>
			<p>
				If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can reach out via 
                my GitHub profile at <a href="https://github.com/alienzj">github.com/alienzj</a>.
			</p>
		</section>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.legal-container {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	section {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
	}

	h2 {
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
		padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
	}

    p {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    }

    a {
        color: var(--accent);
        text-decoration: underline;
    }
</style>
